This paper deals with natural language processing and social media analysis, which are the main topics of the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also utilizes graph theory concepts, which falls under the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) sub-categories. The paper involves information retrieval and summarization, which are the main topics of the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with social media analysis and storytelling, which falls under the cs.SOCIAL (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
